<https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/hazardtype/disease> <http://www.w3.org/ns/adms#status> <http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/registry/status/valid> <https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/hazardtype:1> .
<https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/hazardtype/shockwave> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A shockwave carries energy from a disturbance through a mediu (solid, liquid, gas) similar to a wave though it travels at much higher speed. It can be a type of extraterrestrial hazard caused by the explosion, e.g. airburst or impact of meteorites that generate energy shockwaves capable of shattering glass, collapsing walls, etc."@en <https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/hazardtype:1> .
