<https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/hazardtype/disease> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Either an unusual, often sudden, increase in the number of incidents of an infectious disease that already existed in the region (e.g., flu, E.coli) or the appearance of an infectious disease previously absent from the region, e.g., plague, polio."@en <https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/hazardtype:1> .
