<https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/hazardtype/rockFall> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Rockfall is the primary formational process, occurring either through the release of individual blocks or through larger-scale rockwall collapse, and exerts first-order control over the morphologic development of alpine hillslopes (Ballantyne and Harris, 1994, p. From: Treatise on Geomorphology, 2013"@en <https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/hazardtype:1> .
