<https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/hazardtype/energeticParticles> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Emissions from solar radiation storms consisting of pieces of matter (e.g., protons and other charged particles) moving at very high speed. The magnetosphere and atmosphere block (solar) energetic particles (SEP) from reaching humans on Earth but they are damaging to the electronics of space-borne technology (such as satellites) and pose a radiation hazard to life in space and aircrafts travelling at high altitudes."@en <https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/hazardtype:1> .
<https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/hazardtype/wind> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Air in motion relative to the surface of the earth."@en <https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/hazardtype:1> .
