<https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/hazardtype/tropicalCyclone> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "tropical cyclone originates over tropical or subtropical waters . It is characteri sed by a war m-core, non-frontal synoptic-scale cyclone with a low pressure centre, spiral rain bands and strong winds. Depending on their location, tropical cyclones are referred to as hurricanes (Atlantic, Nort heast Pacific), typhoons (Nort hwest Pacific), or cyclones (South Pacific and Indian Ocean"@en <https://registry.inspire.gv.at/codelist/hazardtype:1> .
